entries.meaning: A check pattern that is superimposed upon another pattern
A strap that stretches from the pollstrap of the bridle to the saddle

verbs.description: overcheck (third-person singular simple present overchecks, present participle overchecking, simple past and past participle overchecked)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To check or verify more than necessary.
examples: When making a trade, err on the side of overchecking the contract details.
